 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "WritingInstrumentAdvisor ⊣ Writing Instrument Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. ISIC
 3290 (Other manufacturing n.e.c.) is a broad residual manufacturing
 category (e.g. brooms/brushes, umbrellas, buttons, pens/pencils,
 artificial flowers); this build's concrete illustration is
 pen/pencil/writing-instrument manufacturing -- a PLANT OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for injection-molding/assembly lines producing
 finished ballpoint pens, pencils, markers, and fountain pens -- not
 direct molding/assembly-line-equipment control authority and not a
 materials-safety-certification (e.g. ACMI AP/CL seal under ASTM
 D4236, or an equivalent national/regional standard) authority. Four
 ops (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Thirteen concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct
 molding/assembly-line-equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate
 block, permanent materials-safety-certification-authority block (this
 actor never self-issues an ACMI AP/CL / ASTM D4236 materials-safety
 compliance certification), independent plant-equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own
 logged production quantity, double-schedule guard, product-type
 validation, materials-safety-pass-percent plausibility validation
 (ink/pigment/solvent toxicity and labeling compliance testing),
 batch-weight plausibility validation, and defect-rate plausibility
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (materials-safety -- ink/pigment
 toxicity, solvent exposure -- or equipment-safety concern) ALWAYS
 escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the
 only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
